  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Reinforcement Learning
Category:    Paradigm
Definition:  Agent learns from environment interaction to maximize reward
Year:        1950
Researchers: Bellman; Sutton/Barto
Applications:Games, robotics, recommendations, LLM alignment
Related:     Reward, policy, value function, Q-learning

Concept:     Fine-tuning
Category:    Training technique
Definition:  Updates pre-trained model weights on task-specific data
Year:        2018
Researchers: Howard/Ruder (ULMFiT)
Applications:Customizing LLMs, domain adaptation
Related:     Supervised fine-tuning, PEFT, LoRA

Concept:     Backpropagation
Category:    Training
Definition:  Computes gradients via chain rule through network layers
Year:        1986
Researchers: Rumelhart/Hinton
Applications:Training all neural networks
Related:     Gradient descent, automatic differentiation

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Fundamental Theorem of Calculus
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      ∫[a,b] f'(x)dx = f(b) - f(a)
Applications: Physics, engineering, economics
Discoverer:   Newton/Leibniz (1670)

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

